post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It would be unethical to bring in revenue from taxing drugs as it exploits those who suffer from addiction.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A family member may stop working to aid them and thus stop \\(otherwise\\) contributing to society and paying taxes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Established companies selling drugs could be just as dangerous \\(to society\\) as criminals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "But we don't make moral judgements all the time every day. We all need to stop thinking clearly and rationally every now and then, for activities including but not limited to play, fun, pleasure, love, chilling out, taking a load offâ€¦ So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Thousands of people [are killed](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/mexicos-drug-war) annually by drug cartels.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs could make people live and learn life as it is. Bad decisions are a part of life.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would be more difficult to use to drugs as a mean of coercion if there would be legal ways of obtaining them and no need to hide the use of narcotics as it would no longer be illegal. Prostitutes would not need criminals to gain access to drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a [correlation](https://americanaddictioncenters.org/rehab-guide/addiction-and-violence) between drug use and \\(violent\\) crime.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has been used as a racist policy to mass incarcerate people of color.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs may also alter the strength of which learning \\(permanent changes of neural activity\\) reacts to such rewards.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are an experience that can build character.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It doesn't mean that we should endanger people and harm them in order for them to not feel safe. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A high level of correlation does not indicate which of the variables is the cause and which is the effect. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When people overdose on illegal drugs medical staff may have a problem knowing what's in the drugs that were ingested. If drugs were legal and regulated, they could save more lives."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Much of this revenue may be attributed to people who became addicted before they were aware of the negative health consequences. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal consumption of heroin without any satisfactory hygiene conditions [supports](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/why-are-heroin-users-special-risk-contracting-hivaids-hepatitis-b-c) the development of HIV.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The war on drugs has [cost civilian lives](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are highly addictive; [addiction is defined as a disease](https://www.centeronaddiction.org/what-addiction/addiction-disease) by most medical associations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no mention](https://www.leafly.com/news/cannabis-101/cannabis-and-the-constitution-a-brief-history-of-cannabis-in-the-u-s) of cannabis, nor any other drugs, in the Constitution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs have recreational and social value.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Private companies have a history of funding advertising supporting the use of products that are known to be dangerous to one's health, such as tobacco. I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Inappropriate recreational drug use has negative health consequences. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Self-medication, for instance with [analgesics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analgesic), will worsen the disease and delay proper treatment. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This essentially places the onus of care back on the government to regulate to keep users safe. If the idea is the government should not control what we do with our bodies this proposition does not really make sense.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That is not an effect of drugs. It can be argued that the neglect of children living with addicted parents is caused by the lack of welfare and safety net, and its effect can probably be lessened if addictions are treated as a healthcare problem. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use will not cease regardless of the legal status. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In a free society, drug users must be free to share their perspective with others, and other people must be free to decide for themselves how they want to act.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since adults would prefer the legal market, these people would have to base their entire business on selling to underaged people. This would make it drastically less profitable, as well as easier to expose by police.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legislators should not be supporting or incentivising the use of any drug that leads to hallucinating and or violence. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "By legalizing and maintaining the produce of drugs for recreational use, the risk of users getting a hold of a drug falsely advertised for being something else when it's rather poisonous would never happen. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Criminals are not interested in drugs, their core interest is money. To gain the largest amount of money, in the quickest time, with the least effort, is their ultimate goal. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
